deck: Josephine Montilyet was the ambassador and chief diplomat of the reformed Inquisition. She is the eldest daughter and heir of the noble Montilyet family from Antiva.
description:
Origin

Josephine Montilyet, also known as Lady Josephine Cherette Montilyet hails from Antiva City, the eldest daughter of a noble family. The Montilyet family having a long and rich history, in the naval business. In her earlier years, Josephine was a Bard, however as in the nature of the bard life in Thedas, although exciting, it meant she would come into conflict, and after another bard threatened her with violence, and she defended herself, she would accidentally kill the man. Later she would realize that other bard, was someone she knew, when she removed his mask.

Josephine as an old friend of Leliana would join the growing and powerful faction, the Inquisition, a movement organized after several unfortunate events in Thedas. She would act as the ambassador of the Inquisition, alongside Cassandra, Leliana, Cullen and several other individuals, looking to bring positive change to Thedas, notably Orlais and Fereldan.

Creation

Josephine Montilyet is a fictional character created for the Dragon Age franchise, written by Sylvia Feketekuty. She appears in various Dragon Age related comic books.

Character Evolution

Josephine Montilyet is an important figure in the Dragon Age Inquisition story.
name: Josephine Montilyet

deck: Leliana, also known as Sister Nightingale, is an Orlesian bard who came to the village of Lothering to become a Sister of the Chantry. There she met the Warden and became one of his/her companiens. After the end of the Fifth Blight, Leliana had become the Left Hand and Spymaster of Divine Justinia V. It was shortly after the death of the Divine, when Leliana joined the reformed Inquisition in order to defeat Corypheus.
description:
Origin

Leliana has been an Orlesian bard, Hero, Spymaster, Left Hand of the Divine, among many over things. Leliana's first memories of her youth, are when she was four, and of her mother, as they stood on an Orlesian terrace overlooking the Waking Sea in Orlais. She remembers the sweet scent of oranges and lavender, but mostly the scent of her mother, Oisine's dress. Its a cherished memory to Leliani as her mother would pass away not long after. Although Leliana would grow up in Orlais, and for all intents and purposes, sound and appear Orlesian, her mother being Fereldan, meant Leliana would hold that part of her close to her heart as well.

After the passing of her mother, Leliana would be looked after by Lady Cecilie Vasseur, the employer of her mother Oisine. Although not related to her by blood, Lady Cecilie Vasseur had a softness and sweet spot towards Leliana. She was also subsequently saddened when the bright, cheerful, little girl Leliana was, turned solemn and sad, with her mothers passing. Lady Cecilie Vasseur would spoil Leliana, giving her anything she asked for, hoping to see her regain her happiness and smile again.

Leliana would only ask for books and stories, and through this she would develop a love for stories, the young girl escaping into worlds of fantasy. The wealth of Lady Cecilie Vasseur, would lead to Leliana being taught by tutors in various disciplines, dancing for example. In her later teenage years, Leliana would encounter a figure that would be very integral to her future, a woman Marjolaine. Marjolaine would gift Leliana a bow, and instruct her on how to use it, thus starting out Leliana's ability to fight as a rogue.

Creation

Leliana is a fictional character created for Dragon Age franchise, by Bioware. The character first appears in the first of the video games of the franchise, Dragon Age Origins, which also includes downloadable content in which she is the lead protagonist. Leliana would also appear in later installments of the video games as well as appear in other media the franchise has spread to, novels and comics included.

Character Evolution

Leliana has experienced much growth and change throughout her stories. Originally quite an optimistic character, who a love of sharing stories, she would progress into being more secretive, cynical and weary in later years.
name: Leliana

deck: A former partner with Carl Ferris during the pre-Crisis universe.
description: Prior to WWII, he was once a partner with Carl Ferris in the Ferris-Bloch Air Inc. Conrad was the flyer while Carl Ferris ran the business. As the years went by, Conrad fell behind in payments and was given one week to come up with his share of the money. Conrad couldn't so Carl Ferris took sole control of Ferris Aircraft Inc. The loss of Ferris-Bloch Air Inc. caused a downward spiral in Conrad's life. He took it out on his wife Edith causing her to leave him three years later. Conrad began to drink heavily until it nearly costed him his life. After beating the drinking habit, Conrad took restock on his life and invested what money he had into a small time air cargo company. The company grew and ultimately became Bloch Air Inc. The company invested heavily into a solar jet, but Ferris Air had created a solar jet too. The government awarded a contract to Ferris Air and Bloch Air went bankrupt. Conrad in a dire attempt to save his company tried to sabotage Ferris Air's solar jet program. In an attempt to destroy the prototype jet Conrad was caught in the blast which disfigured him for life. Conrad was married to Edith Bloch and they had two sons Congressman Jason Bloch and Benjamin Bloch who works for Bloch Air.
